===Other statistics===

* Fourth most wins out of all active NHL goaltenders
* [[Six]] time leader of the NHL in save percentage
* Ranks [[10]]th in the NHL all-time in shutouts, and 15th all-time in wins.
* Most NHL shutouts in one month (six in 97-98)
* Personal best shutout streak of 181 minutes, 17 seconds<ref>{{cite web
| title = Hasek sets career-best NHL shutout streak
| url = http://www.iht.com/articles/ap/2006/11/15/sports/NA_SPT_HKY_NHL_Red_Wings_Hasek.php
| date = 2006-11-15
| access date = 2006-11-15
}}
</ref>
==All-Star honours==

* Named to the NHL first All-star Team five times (1993-94, 1995, 1996-97, 1997-98, 1998-99)
* [[NHL All-Rookie Team]]: 1991-92 
* [[All-Star Game]]: 1996, 1997, 1998, 1999, 2000 (did not play due to [[injury]])
* [[Hockey News]] All-Star First Team: 1996-97
* [[Sporting News]] All-Star First Team: 1995, 1996-97, 1997-98 
* Sporting News All-Star Second Team: 1993-94
* [[Beckett Hockey]] [[Magazine]] All-Star First Team: 1993-94 

===SuperSkills competition===

* Overall Goalie Champion: 1996, 1998, 2002 - tie
* [[Breakaway]] Relay Goalie Champion: 1996, 1997, 1998, 1999, 2002
* Rapid Fire Goalie Champion: 1996, 1998 - tie [http://www.hockeydraftcentral.com/1983/83199.html]

==International play==
[[Image:0222 hockey1.jpg|thumb|right|Hašek in goal at the gold medal game against Russia. He earned a shutout in a 1-0 victory]]
Hašek's most memorable international performance came in [[Ice hockey at the 1998 Winter Olympics|the 1998 Olympics]]. He was stellar throughout the tournament, allowing six goals in total&mdash;only two of which were in the medal round. Against Team Canada, Hašek stopped Canada's [[Theoren Fleury]], [[Ray Bourque]], [[Joe Nieuwendyk]], [[Eric Lindros]], and [[Brendan Shanahan]] in the shootout win.
Hašek led the [[Czech national ice hockey team|Czech team]] to the [[gold medal]], shutting out the [[Russian national ice hockey team|Russian team]] 1-0 in the final game, stopping 20 shots. Hašek was overjoyed. After he won the gold, he was quoted as saying, <blockquote>"When the game ended, I just threw my stick. I was so happy. When I saw the flag go up, I saw my whole career flash before my eyes from the first time my parents took me to a game until now."<ref>
{{cite news
| last = Alexander
| first = Rachel
| title = For Cap's Gonchar, a Silver Lining
| publisher = The Washington Post
| date = 1998-02-22
| url = http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-srv/sports/longterm/olympics1998/sport/hockey/articles/gonchar23.htm
| accessdate = 2006-08-05}}</ref> </blockquote>

His play made him arguably one of the most popular figures in the Czech Republic; his reputation is comparable to that of then-president [[Václav Havel]].<ref>
{{cite web
  | title = Q&A: Czech hockey goalie Dominik Hasek
  | publisher = Canadian Broadcasting Corporation
  | date = 2006-02-03
  | url = http://www.cbc.ca/olympics/stories/indepth.shtml?/story/olympics/national/2006/02/01/Sports/hasek-qa060201.html
  | accessdate = 2006-08-07 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web
| last = Wolloughby
| first = Ian
| title = Dominator for president!
| date = 2003-02-03
| url = http://www.radio.cz/en/article/37267
| accessdate = 2006-08-14}}</ref>
He also helped to inspire an opera (titled ''Nagano'') about the Czech team's gold medal victory,<ref>
{{cite web
| last = Asiedu
| first = Dita
| title = "Nagano" Opera premieres at Prague's Estates Theatre
| url = http://www.radio.cz/en/article/52625
| date = 2004-09-04
| accessdate = 2006-08-14}}</ref>
and, in 2003, [[Petr Pravec]] and [[Lenka Šarounová]] named an [[asteroid]] ([[8217 Dominikhašek]]) in his honour.<ref>
{{cite web
| title = JPL Small-Body Database Browser
| url = http://ssd.jpl.nasa.gov/sbdb.cgi?sstr=8217
| date = 2003-09-23
| access date = 2006-09-02}}</ref>

In the [[2006 Winter Olympics]] in [[Turin]], [[Italy]], he played for just 9:25, until he injured his right [[Adductor muscles of the hip|adductor muscle]]. His team managed to earn a bronze medal, which Hašek received as well.

